`CopyToClipboardTableCell` and `CopyToClipboardListItem` share a lot of the same code. We should try to avoid rewriting duplicate code. One way to do this is to write a react hook. For example, we can create a file `src/utils/useCopyToClipboard.js` with the following content:

```jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from 'react';

function useCopyToClipboard() {
  const [isCopy, setCopy] = useState(false);

  function handleCopyClick() {
    setCopy(true);
  }

  useEffect(() => {
    if (isCopy) {
      setTimeout(() => {
        setCopy(false);
      }, 3000);
    }
  }, [isCopy]);

  return {
    onCopyClick: handleCopyClick,
    isCopy,
  };
}

export default useCopyToClipboard;
```

We would then need to make use of this file in both files. For example, in `CopyToClipboardTableCell`, we would do:

```diff
