Actually, just found something we should fix here. This should be a `cudaMemsetAsync` and pass in the stream from `device_context->stream()` or else the `cudaMemset` will launched in the default CUDA stream and cause undesired device-wide synchronization behavior. I think using this particular stream should ensure the memset occurs after the TF tensor is allocated. The call needs to be something like:
```
auto device_context = context_->op_device_context();
auto stream = (device_context != nullptr) ? AsGpuStreamValue(device_context->stream()) : 0;
cudaMemsetAsync((void*)zero_tensor->AccessTensor(hvd_context->GetKernelContext())->tensor_data().data(), 0, 
                zero_tensor->AccessTensor(hvd_context->GetKernelContext())->tensor_data().size(), stream);
```
@tgaddair can you also comment on this? I am not as well versed in this part of the code, but this seems to be the behavior we want. I'm also not quite clear on when `context_->op_device_context()` could be `nullptr` if running on GPU.

