in general it makes more sense to me to add type hints to member variables in the class declaration. that way you can get the type hints through the `__annotations__` magic var (which can be helpful for docs and other reflective mechanisms): 

```python
class Foo:
    bar: str

    def __init__(self):
        self.baz: int = 0

if __name__ == '__main__':
    print(Foo.__annotations__)
```
will output `{'bar': <class 'str'>}`
